# YouTube Automation — Ambient/Soundscape Channel
# Full-stack AI agent system managed by NemoClaw

---

## Project Overview

We are building an AI-powered YouTube automation system that runs an ambient/soundscape channel
(rain sounds, lo-fi, fireplace, dark forest, coffee shop ambiance, nature audio, etc.).
The goal is side income of $500–$2k/month through YouTube AdSense, channel memberships, and affiliate links.
The system is designed to operate autonomously with minimal human intervention.

The stack has two layers:

1. **The factory** — a Next.js 14 (App Router) dashboard + CrewAI Python backend running 6 specialized agents
2. **The manager** — a NemoClaw OpenClaw agent that sits above everything, monitors the system,
   makes high-level decisions, and communicates updates via Telegram

---

## Architecture

```
NemoClaw (OpenClaw agent — always-on autonomous manager)
  - Reads analytics reports and agent outputs
  - Makes high-level strategic decisions
  - Sends Telegram updates / asks for human approval
  - Can update agent instructions and priorities
  - Runs in an isolated OpenShell sandbox (network + filesystem policy enforced)
        ↓  manages & instructs via API
Next.js Dashboard (control plane UI)
        ↓
CrewAI Python Backend (agent execution layer)
  ├── Strategy Agent      — reads all reports, sets content priorities, runs the ROI loop
  ├── Research Agent      — YouTube trends, RPM by niche, competition density, keyword data
  ├── Content Agent       — titles, thumbnails, descriptions, tags
  ├── Production Agent    — audio loop generation, visual assembly, FFmpeg rendering
  ├── Upload Agent        — YouTube Data API v3, scheduling, metadata posting
  └── Analytics Agent     — watch time, RPM, CTR, subscriber conversion — reports back
        ↓
External Tools & APIs
  - YouTube Data API v3
  - SerpAPI (trend research)
  - Suno API (original audio generation)
  - ElevenLabs (voice if needed)
  - DALL·E / Replicate (thumbnail visuals)
  - FFmpeg (video rendering)
  - Redis (shared agent memory + run history)
  - Supabase (persistent storage — analytics, content history, agent logs)
```

