## Tech Stack

### Frontend
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui
- **State**: Zustand
- **Data fetching**: TanStack Query (React Query)
- **Charts**: Recharts (for analytics dashboard)
- **Real-time**: Supabase Realtime (agent activity feed)

### Backend (Python)
- **Agent framework**: CrewAI
- **Language**: Python 3.11+
- **API layer**: FastAPI (Next.js talks to this)
- **Task queue**: Celery + Redis
- **Memory**: Redis (short-term), Supabase (long-term)
- **Video rendering**: FFmpeg via subprocess
- **Environment**: `.env` for all secrets, `pydantic-settings` for config

### NemoClaw Layer
- **Runtime**: OpenShell sandbox (via `nemoclaw onboard`)
- **Agent**: OpenClaw agent with custom instructions and tools
- **Inference**: NVIDIA Nemotron 3 Super 120B via build.nvidia.com (can switch at runtime)
- **Communication**: Telegram bridge (native NemoClaw deployment option)
- **Policy**: Custom `openclaw-sandbox.yaml` — allowlisted endpoints only
- **Tools given to OpenClaw agent**:
  - Read analytics reports from Supabase
  - Call Next.js API routes to trigger agent runs
  - Read/write agent priority instructions
  - Send Telegram messages to the human operator

### Infrastructure
- **Hosting**: Vercel (Next.js) + Railway or Render (FastAPI + Celery)
- **Database**: Supabase (Postgres + Realtime + Storage)
- **Cache/Queue**: Redis (Upstash)
- **GPU (if needed)**: NVIDIA GPU instance via NemoClaw remote deployment

