## Coding Conventions

- TypeScript strict mode always on
- All API routes use Zod for input validation
- All agent outputs are typed with Pydantic models
- Never hardcode secrets — always use environment variables
- All async operations use proper error handling (try/catch + typed errors)
- Supabase calls always use the service role key on the server, anon key on the client
- FFmpeg subprocess calls always run inside a try/except with timeout
- Agent logs are always written to Supabase `agent_runs` table with timestamp, agent name, status, output summary

